title: For Sale:  Romanian WASR 10/63 UF 7.62x39 - Excellent Cond
postcontent: This rifle is in excellent condition. I've taken very good care of it and doubt I have more than 30-50 rounds through it. I've owned this rifle since it was new. This rifle was not built by Century Arms. It was built in Romania and imported by Century Arms. It does have the original chrome-lined, cold-hammer-forged barrel and it looks new - having strong rifling and a nice shiny bore. WASRs are known to have issues such as canted sights, mag wobble etc. This rifle has zero issues. Let me state this again - this rifle has zero issues. Everything is perfectly straight, the bolt/bolt carrier rides smoothly on the rails and a variety of mags lock in nice and tight. I only shot this rifle on one occasion and, aside from that, it's been collecting dust. When I did shoot this rifle, I used iron sights and was able to consistently get 3-4" groups at 100 yards with Golden Tiger and Tula. Included with this rifle will be a Tapco Saw OD Green Grip, Tapco Intrafuse OD Green forend, cleaning rod, rifle sling, Romanian forend, bayonet and grip (see the last two photos that I've provided). This particular rifle was finished in ALuma-Hyde II Matte Black. If you are not familiar with Aluma-Hyde II, it is awesome. The stuff is very durable and looks great as you can see in my photos. Do a quick Google search and find out for yourself. Most of the complaints you'll find will be the price (nearly all other complaints stem from people not following Brownell's instructions), but aside from that, it's good to go.I did not repaint this rifle for any other reason than to cover up that unsightly Romanian finish. It wasn't horrible, but it wasn't amazing either and I am very picky when it comes to my firearms. If you are familiar with Romanian rifles, you'll know what I mean. Most of their rifles are great from a fit and function standpoint, but majority of the time, the finish leaves much to be desired. One thing that seems to wear out from shooting these is the underfolder hinge/trunnion. However, that's not really an issues since I have barely shot (or even handled) this rifle. The stock on this rifle has little to no play and locks up tight when open or closed. I am confident that this is the nicest WASR you'll find on GunBroker. It is my understanding that WASR UFs are no longer being imported. This rifle will come with one 30-round steel mag. If you would like extra mags, I will include them for $20 per mag. That's cheaper than they can be found anywhere as far as I have seen. I will sell you a maximum of four extra mags with this rifle as I do not have a ton of mags.The 6 US parts on this rifle are the muzzle brake, trigger group, grip, and forend. This keeps the rifle in compliance with 922r and will allow you to use any foreign mag in this rifle without being in violation of 922r.. Email me if you have any questions, Thank You

Automatic Indexing
Each station moves 1/2 a stage on the upstroke and 1/2 a stage on the down stroke and the up stroke, making for ultra-smooth function. This process is much smoother than presses that do all their indexing on the down stroke.


Large Capacity Hopper
